						               													<description>The players have to play different roles in this game. Each player is reading another player's mind and cheating each other. If the rich man hides a treasure tile, he can win. On the other hand, if the thief finds it, he can win. If you acquire 8 gem tokens first, you win.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;--Objective--&amp;#10;The Rich Man: Make The Thief face up the predetermined number of cards before The Thief finds the treasure tile.&amp;#10;The Thief: Find the treasure tile before facing up the predetermined number of cards.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;--Set up--&amp;#10;The Rich Man put the 8 door tiles. He hides 1 treasure tile in them. (He only knows the place of the treasure tile.)&amp;#10;&amp;#10;--Course of play--&amp;#10;1. The Rich Man places a card face up on the door tile. &amp;#10;2. The Thief faces up a door tile.&amp;#10;If the attribute of the door tile is equal to the attribute of the card, the card gives an effect for players.&amp;#10;The cards have several effects. Some cards are advantage of The Rich Man and the other cards are advantage of The Thief.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from the designer&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
